Other Technologies
We may use other technologies, including web beacons and JavaScript, which sometimes work together with cookies and other means with our Sites and Mobile Apps to uniquely identify your device. These other technologies help enable features on our Sites and within our Mobile Apps.
We may also use certain technologies to determine whether you have opened an e-mail or clicked on a link contained in an e-mail.
Where video is available on our Online Services, we may target and track the videos you view. You consent to our tracking of your video viewing through Online Services or third-party social media for up to two years, or as permitted by the applicable law, or until consent is withdrawn.
Targeted Advertising
On our Online Services, we may collect information about your online activities for use in providing you with advertising tailored to your individual interests, provided you have opted-in to marketing communications. This section of our Privacy Statement provides details and explains how to manage your choices.
You may see certain advertisements on other websites because we participate in advertising networks. Advertising networks allow us to target our messaging to users through demographic, interest-based and contextual means. These networks track your online activities over time by collecting information through automated means, including through the use of cookies, web server logs, web beacons and other technologies. The networks use this information to show you advertisements that may be tailored to your individual interests. The information our advertising networks may collect includes information about your visits to websites that participate in the relevant advertising networks, such as the pages or advertisements you view and the actions you take on the websites. This data collection takes place both on our Online Services and on third-party websites that participate in the advertising networks. This process also helps us evaluate our marketing efforts.
Links to Other Websites and Social Media
Our Online Services may offer links to third-party websites that are not operated by McDonald's. If you visit one of these linked websites, you should review the website's privacy policy, terms and conditions, and other policies. We are not responsible for the policies and practices of third-parties. Any information you submit to these third-parties is subject to their privacy policy, terms and conditions, and other policies.
Information Security
McDonald's is committed to taking appropriate measures designed to keep personal information secure. We have in place organizational, technical, administrative, and physical procedures designed to protect personal information from accidental, unlawful or unauthorized destruction or loss, unauthorized dissemination, access, disclosure, use, alteration, or corruption and any other form of unlawful processing. Such measures aim to ensure a level of security which is analogous to the risks involved in the processing and the nature of the personal information being processed. While we take every effort to safeguard our information systems, no website, mobile application, computer system, or transmission of data over the Internet or any other public network can be guaranteed to be 100% secure.
Retention of Personal Information
We retain personal information for the period of time necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Statement and per McDonald's records retention policies which have been designed to abide with the GDPR and in particular the data minimization principle unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
Our Company’s retention policy related to
McDelivery customers
placing orders via Call Center, has been designed to maintain the data, only if the customer has provided his consent to do so and as long as the person is considered an “active” McDelivery customer.
For
McDelivery Mobile Application
or
Online customers
, our Company’s retention policy has been designed to maintain the data, only if the customer is registered as
McDelivery
Customer
and as long as the person is considered an “active” McDelivery customer.
A person is considered an “active”
McDelivery
customer
as long as he has placed a McDelivery Order (from any phone number and for any address, related with his account) within the last 12 months.
Our Company’s retention policy related to
McDonald’s Mobile application (GMALite)
, has been designed to maintain the data, only if the customer has provided his consent to do so and as long as the person is considered an “active” McDonald’s customer.
A person is considered an “active”
McDonald’s
customer
as long as he has redeemed an Offer within the last 12 months.
Our company’s retention policy related to
BirthdayLine
customers, has been designed to maintain the data until fifteen (15) days after the birthday party has taken place.
Images of the
CCTV
system will be recorded and kept for a minimum of 7 days. Any footage that shows a crime will be kept as long as it is needed to undertake criminal proceedings. Any footage that shows an incident which the individual has accused the Company or has been accused by the Company, will be kept as long as needed to undertake the legal procedures.
McDonald’s also captures your image at the time you place your order in Drive Thru. Image received at the time of placing your order in Drive Thru is not permanently saved onto any device but contributing to Operational Effectiveness by matching the correct order to the correct person.
Recordings
Calls are being recorded for safeguarding our legitimate interest and for service quality improvement. Recordings are kept for the period of 2 (two) months and then deleted. Call recording containing customer’s consent, is kept until the customer is no longer considered “active” (definition of “active” has been provided above).
