Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy
Thank you for visiting us at McDonalds.com.hk, purchasing at McDonald’s or using our service. At McDonald’s®, we strive to do everything we can to respect the trust our customers have in our brand and our commitment to protect your privacy is no exception. We are committed to protecting and safeguarding consumer privacy, especially for children.
McDonald’s Privacy Policy
McDonald’s Hong Kong (“McDonald’s”) is pleased to provide information on our privacy policy. Please be assured that McDonald’s uses its best efforts to protect your privacy.
Types of Information We Collect and How It Is Used
McDonald’s only gathers personal information, including but not limited to, first and last names, phone numbers, addresses and email addresses, when voluntarily submitted by you. Personal information collected from you will only be used for the purposes for which it is collected and for other directly related purposes, including but not limited to, (a) obtaining your feedback and handling your enquiry on our web sites, applications software for mobile devices, products and services; (b) entering you in any of our contests or sweepstakes; (c) processing your orders and payments; (d) verification of identity and updating our records; (e) generating surveys on user traffic; and (f) for direct marketing purposes by providing you with news update on our products, services and promotional events or other marketing materials or information such as discount coupons (“direct marketing”).
By your submission of your personal information for the purposes for which it is collected, it indicates that you have read and understood this privacy policy and you are consenting to our collection and use of your personal information in association with all purposes described in this policy. However, we may not use your personal information, including your name and contact details, in direct marketing unless we have received your express consent. If you would like to receive news updates on our products, services and promotional events or other marketing materials or information about us, please indicate your consent by checking the tick box on the form you use to submit your personal information to us or by orally notifying us of your consent when you provide your personal information to us otherwise than in writing. If after providing us with your consent you decide you no longer want us to use your personal information in direct marketing, please let us know by contacting us at the email or postal address listed at the end of this policy and we will desist.
Sharing of Personal Information
McDonald's may share personal information within the McDonald's Family. The McDonald's Family includes McDonald’s Hong Kong, its parent corporations, shareholding companies, its subsidiaries, affiliates and franchisees. Any use of personal information by the McDonald's Family will comply with this policy. We may provide your personal information, including your name and contact details, to entities of the McDonald's Family in direct marketing, and we may not do so unless we have received your consent. If you do not want us to provide your personal information to the McDonald's Family for direct marketing purposes, please let us know by contacting us at the email or postal address listed at the end of this policy and we will desist.
McDonald's may engage companies outside the McDonald's Family to perform a variety of functions, such as, fulfilling orders, assisting with promotions and market surveys, providing technical services for our web sites and applications software, etc. These companies may have to be provided with access to personal information collected by McDonald's to perform such functions. However, these companies may only use such personal information for the purpose of performing that function and may not use it for any other purpose.
McDonald's may share or need to transfer personal information to entities of the McDonald's Family or companies engaged by McDonald's to perform the functions described above, which are located in countries or jurisdictions outside of Hong Kong. The laws governing data protection in these countries or jurisdictions may differ from the laws in Hong Kong. McDonald's will comply with the laws of Hong Kong on data protection to ensure that similar and/or comparable standards for data protection under these laws are maintained by the overseas entities of the McDonald's Family and overseas companies which are recipient of your personal data. By your voluntary submission of personal information to us, you are consenting to the disclosure, transfer and use of your personal information outside of Hong Kong for the purposes described in this policy.
McDonald's does not sell, transfer or disclose personal information to third parties outside the McDonald's Family save as mentioned above. However, with your permission, we will, on occasion send marketing materials on behalf of our business partners on their products or services which may be of interest to you. You will be asked if you wish to receive marketing materials from these McDonald's business partners. If you elect to receive such marketing materials, McDonald's will not share your personal information with such partners but will rather send a communication to you on behalf of such partners.
McDonald's reserves the right to use or disclose any information as needed to satisfy any law, regulation or legal request, to protect the integrity of the site, to fulfill your requests, or to cooperate in any law enforcement investigation or an investigation on a matter of public safety.
Our Privacy Policy Regarding Children
McDonald's is very conscious of privacy issues. We are proud of our longtime commitment to our customers. We are especially careful in any communications with one of our most treasured customers – children.
On our web sites, we may offer many features, such as games and coloring books, which do not require children to provide any personal information. We collect only limited personal information from children of age 12 or under (such as their email addresses) to respond to their online requests. For example, we may collect a child's email address in order to send the child a screen saver, but we will promptly delete the email address from our system thereafter. Or, we may collect a child's email address in order to enter the child in sweepstakes. We may also ask a child to provide an email address of his/her parent so we can notify the parent or seek consent. We will not collect more detailed information from any child of age 12 or younger, such as postal address or telephone number, without the consent of his/her parent or guardian. McDonald's will not condition a child's participation in any online activity on the child's disclosure of more personal information than is reasonably necessary to participate in that activity.
Personal information collected from children is used solely by McDonald's or other entities that provide McDonald's with technical, fulfillment or other services to McDonald's. For example, such entities may provide services, such as, improving our web sites, fulfilling requests or administering sweepstakes. Personal information so collected is not sold or transferred to third parties.
We urge parents to regularly monitor and supervise their children's on-line activities.
Mobile Application
Under normal circumstances, we do not actively collect personal data of underage persons.  However, as birthday is not compulsory information and we would normally not request age proof from customers, we cannot verify customers’ age.  If you are under-age, please obtain the approval from your guardian before using any internal platforms and services of McDonald’s.  If your guardian does not agree your using of McDonald’s services under this policy or provision of personal data with McDonald’s, please stop proceeding further.  If you have registered and set up an account on McDonald’s mobile application, please stop using McDonald’s service and inform us through the contact details at the end of this policy, to enable us to take any appropriate actions.  If you are a guardian, please fulfil your duty properly and protect the personal data of under-age persons.  If an under-age person would like to register or use our service/products, please provide he or she with proper guidance and supervision.  If there is proof that any under-age persons have registered and use our product or service without the approval of his or her guardian, the relevant guardian please inform us as soon as possible for discussion of the next step.
Access
You are in control of all personal information you provide to us. If at any time, you would like to review, correct or change the personal information we have on you or your child, or to change your preferences for contacts from us or on behalf of our business partners, you may let us know by submitting an information request form as provided below or contacting us at the email or postal address listed at the end of this policy.
In order to review any personal information we have about you or to ask us to delete that information or to stop further use of the information, please submit this information request form. (See attached
Privacy Information Request Form
.)
In order to review any personal information we have about your child or to ask us to delete that information or to stop further use of the information, please submit this information request form. (See attached
Child Privacy Information Request Form
.)
Cookies
"Cookies" are pieces of information that a web site transfers to an individual's hard drive for record-keeping purposes. Cookies allow the web site to remember important information that will make your use of the site more convenient. Like most web sites, McDonald's uses cookies for a variety of purposes in order to improve your online experience. For example, we track the total number of visitors to our site on an anonymous aggregate basis. We may also employ cookies so that we remember you when you return to the site, to keep track of the items in your shopping cart if you purchase merchandise online, to administer certain contests and sweepstakes and to help customize your McDonald's web experience. We may associate personal information with a cookie file in those instances.
Use the options in your web browser if you do not wish to receive a cookie or if you wish to set your browser to notify you when you receive a cookie. Click on the "Help" section of your browser to learn how to change your cookie preferences. If you disable all cookies, you may not be able to take advantage of all the features of our web site.
Links to Other Sites
We may offer links to sites that are not operated by McDonald's. If you visit one of these linked sites, you should review their privacy and other policies. We are not responsible for the policies and practices of other companies and any information you submit to those companies is subject to their privacy policies.
Other McDonald's Web Sites
All McDonald's web sites operated by McDonald's Corporation will adhere to this privacy policy. The policies of some McDonald's sites may vary, however, because of local customs, practices or laws or due to circumstances unique to that site. In all cases, however, sites operated by McDonald's Corporation will honor the commitments to our customers set forth in this policy regarding the collection and use of personal information.
Changes to our Privacy Policy
This privacy policy is updated as of October 2024. From time to time, it may be necessary for McDonald's to update this policy. If we update our policy, we will post the updated version on our website, so we suggest that you check here periodically for the most up-to-date version of our privacy policy. Rest assured, however, that any changes will not be applied retrospectively and will not alter how we handle information collected earlier.
The English version of this policy shall prevail in case of any discrepancies between the English and Chinese versions.
How to Contact Us
If you have any questions regarding McDonald's Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
McDonald’s Hong Kong
35/F, Dorset House, Taikoo Place,
979 King's Road
Quarry Bay, Hong Kong
(852) 2880 7300
Sub-policy 31
https://mcdonalds.com.hk/privacy-policy/:
個人私隱政策
個人私隱政策
歡迎瀏覽McDonalds.com.hk網站、於麥當勞®消費或使用麥當勞®的服務。為答謝顧客對麥當勞®品牌的信任，麥當勞一直致力履行維護顧客個人私隱的承諾。我們竭力保護和保障顧客的個人私隱，而兒童個人資料的保護尤其重要。
麥當勞的私隱政策
香港麥當勞 (「麥當勞」)誠意向閣下提供有關我們的個人私隱政策詳情。閣下請放心，麥當勞一向竭盡所能保護您的個人私隱。
我們收集的資料種類以及如何使用此等資料
麥當勞只收集閣下自願提供的個人資料，當中包括但不限於您的姓名、電話號碼、地址和電郵地址等等。從您收集得來的個人資料將只用於其收集時所說明的目的和其他直接相關的用途，包括但不限於：(一) 獲取您的意見和處理您對我們的網站、流動通訊裝置軟件、產品和服務的查詢；(二) 邀請您參加我們的競賽遊戲或抽獎活動；(三) 處理您的訂單和付款；(四) 核實身份和更新我們的記錄；(五) 進行用戶流量調查；以及 (六) 為您提供我們產品、服務及推廣活動的最新消息或其他市場資訊（如折扣優惠劵）以作直接促銷用途（"直銷"）。
在您提交您的個人資料以供我們按收集時所說明的目的使用時，則表示您已經閱讀和理解本個人私隱政策，并同意我們收集您的個人資料并將其用於與本政策中所述的所有目的相關的用途。然而，我們不會使用您的個人資料作直銷，包括您的姓名和聯絡方法，除非我們已經收到您明確同意。如果您希望收到我們產品、服務及推廣活動的最新消息或其他市場推廣或我們公司的資訊，請於您提交個人資料的表格上剔選您同意或口頭通知我們您同意（如您並非以書面形式向我們提交個人資料）。如果我們獲取您的同意後，您決定不再希望我們使用您的個人資料作直銷，請透過本政策末段提供之郵寄地址通知我們拒收，以便處理。
共享個人資料
麥當勞可能會於麥當勞家庭成員內共享您的個人資料。麥當勞家庭成員包括香港麥當勞、其母公司、股東公司、其附屬公司、聯營公司和特許經營商。麥當勞家庭成員將在其使用個人資料時遵守本政策。我們可能會向麥當勞家庭成員提供您的個人資料（包括您的姓名和聯絡方法）以作直銷用途。然而，除非得到您的同意，否則我們不得作出上述行為。如果您不希望我們把您的個人資料供給麥當勞家庭成員作直銷用途，請透過本政策末段提供之電郵地址或郵寄地址通知我們，以便處理。
麥當勞亦可能會聘請麥當勞家庭成員以外的其他公司履行各種任務，例如訂單跟進、協助市場推廣和調查、為我們的網站和應用軟件提供技術支援等，這些公司可能需要應用到麥當勞收集的個人資料以執行其任務。然而，這些公司只可將該等個人資料用於履行其任務，不得用於其他用途。
麥當勞可能需要與位於香港以外的國家或司法管轄區的麥當勞家庭成員或麥當勞聘請的公司分享或轉移您的個人資料以讓其履行上述任務。這些國家或司法管轄區的個人資料保障條例可能不同於香港的法律。麥當勞將遵守香港的個人資料（私隱）條例，以確保該等取得您的個人資料的海外的麥當勞和麥當勞聘請的海外公司將給予相似及/或可比程度的個人資料保障。在您自願提交個人資料給我們的情況下，則表示您同意我們向香港以外地區披露、轉移您的個人資料并將其用於本政策所述的用途。
除上述的情況外，麥當勞不會出售、轉讓或披露您的個人資料予麥當勞家庭成員以外的第三者。然而，在您的許可下，我們將代表我們的業務合作夥伴不時發送您可能感興趣的有關他們的產品或服務的市場資訊。如果您選擇接收這些麥當勞業務合作夥伴的市場資訊。麥當勞不會把您的個人資料與這些合作夥伴共享，而會代這些合作夥伴發送其通訊給您。
麥當勞保留使用或披露任何資料的權利，以滿足任何法規或法律的要求，以保護網站的完整性，以滿足您的要求，或以協助司法調查或公眾安全調查的事宜。
我們對兒童的個人私隱政策
麥當勞非常關注私隱保障的重要性。我們對顧客的長期承諾引以為傲。我們要求與我們最珍貴的客戶 —— 兒童溝通時都會格外小心。
我們在我們的網站上可能提供許多功能，如遊戲和彩色電子書，兒童不需要提供任何個人資料便可享用這些功能。我們只收集12歲或以下兒童的有限個人資料（如電郵地址），以回應他們在網上提出的要求。例如，我們可能會收集兒童的電郵地址以向其送出屏幕保護程式，但是我們將在完成送出後立即從我們的系統上刪除其電郵地址。或者，我們可能會因應抽獎活動需要收集兒童的電郵地址。我們也會要求兒童提供他/她的家長的電郵地址以通知家長或徵求同意。我們不會在未經他/她的家長或監護人同意下，向任何12歲或以下兒童收集其郵寄地址或電話號碼等更詳細的個人資料。麥當勞不會以披露超出比正常需要的個人資料為條件以允許兒童參與任何網上活動。
兒童提交的個人資料僅用於麥當勞或其他公司提供技術服務、履行職責或其他服務予麥當勞（如改善我們的網站、執行要求或管理抽獎）。收集的個人資料不會出售或轉讓給第三者。
我們敦促家長定期監測和監督孩子的網上活動。
流動通訊裝置軟件
一般情況下，我們不會主動收集未成年人士的個人資料。但由於生日並不是必須提供的資料，且我們一般不會要求顧客提供年齡證明，我們無法識別顧客的年齡。若您未成年，在您使用任何網絡平臺及麥當勞服務之前，請務必事先取得您的監護人的同意。如您的監護人不同意您按照本政策使用麥當勞的服務或向麥當勞提供您的資料，請您停止繼續；若您已註冊並成為流動通訊裝置軟件用戶，請立即終止使用麥當勞的服務並及時透過文末通訊方式通知我們，以便採取合適的措施。若您是監護人，請正確履行監護職責，保護未成年人士的個人資料安全；若未成年人士本人需要註冊或使用我們的產品與/或服務，您應正確引導並予以監護。如果有事實證明未成年人士在未取得監護人同意的情況下註冊使用了我們的產品或服務，請相關監護人盡快透過文末通訊方式聯絡我們，以商討下一步行動。
查閱個人資料
您能夠控制您提供給我們的所有個人資料。如果您想查閱、糾正或更改您或您的孩子提交給我們的個人資料，或更改我們或我們的業務合作夥伴與您的聯絡方法，您可以透過提交以下的資料申請表或透過本政策未段提供的電郵地址或郵寄地址與我們聯絡。
如要檢查我們關於您的任何個人資料，或要求我們刪除該等資料，或停止進一步使用該等資料，請提交此資料申請表。 （請見附件《私隱資料申請表》。）
如要檢查我們關於您的孩子的任何個人資料，或要求我們刪除該等資料，或停止進一步使用該等資料，請提交此資料申請表。 （請見附件《兒童私隱資料申請表》。）
小型文字檔案（"曲奇檔案"）
"曲奇檔案"是網站為記錄目的傳送到個別電腦硬碟中的資料。曲奇檔案使網站能記憶重要資訊，從而使您能方便地使用網站。像大多數網站一樣，為了改善您的線上體驗，麥當勞將曲奇檔案用於多種用途。例如，我們不記名地記錄我們網站訪客的總人數。我們也使用曲奇檔案以便您再次造訪時讓我們能識別您，如您在線上購物，可以幫助查找您購物車上的項目，管理一些競賽遊戲和抽獎活動，以及幫助制定您的麥當勞個人化網上體驗。在以上情況下我們可能將個人資訊裝入曲奇檔案。
倘若您不想收到曲奇檔案或在收到曲奇檔案時希望瀏覽器通知您，請使用您的線上瀏覽器中的選項。點擊瀏覽器的"幫助"鍵以了解如何更改您的曲奇檔案設定。倘若您禁止所有曲奇檔案，您可能不能充分體會本網站的所有功能。
連接其他網站
我們可能提供連接至其他非由麥當勞管理的網站，倘若您造訪這些網站，您應閱讀他們的個人私隱和其他政策。我們對其他公司的政策或事務不負上任何責任，您所提交的資料將以該公司的私隱政策為依據。
麥當勞的其他網站
所有麥當勞公司經營的網站都將遵守本個人私隱政策。然而，因為有些地方的習俗、慣例或法律不同，或因為某網站的特殊情況，可能導致某些麥當勞網站的政策有所不同。但無論如何，所有麥當勞公司經營的網站都會遵守本政策中有關收集和使用個人資料的承諾。
我們個人私隱政策的更新
本個人私隱政策於2024年10月更新。麥當勞將不時更新本政策。如果我們更新本政策，我們將在網站發布更新的版本，所以我們建議您定期查閱我們私隱政策的最新版本。不過請放心，任何更改將不會有追溯力，並不會改變我們如何處理之前收集的資料。
本政策的中、英文版本發生歧異，以英文版本為準。
如果您對麥當勞的個人私隱政策有任何疑問，請與我們聯絡：
香港麥當勞
香港鰂魚涌英皇道979號
太古坊多盛大廈35/F
(852)2880 7300
Sub-policy 32
https://www.mcdonalds.hu/adatvedelem#app:
ADATKEZELÉSI TÁJÉKOZTATÓ
Letöltöm
<h2>ADATKEZELÉSI TÁJÉKOZTATÓ</h2>
See English version of Privacy Notice valid from 01.01.2025.
1. Bevezetés
A Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. (1027 Budapest, Bem József utca 1/B., a továbbiakban szolgáltató, adatkezelő) mint adatkezelő, illetve a 2.2.1; 2.2.2; 2.4.1; 2.4.2; 2.4.3; 2.5.1; 2.6.3; fejezetekben található adatkezelések tekintetében a Progress Promotion Kft. (1027 Budapest, Bem József utca 1/B.), mint a Progress Étteremhálózat Kft-vel közös adatkezelő magára nézve kötelezőnek ismeri el jelen jogi közlemény tartalmát. Kötelezettséget vállal arra, hogy tevékenységével kapcsolatos minden adatkezelés megfelel a jelen szabályzatban és a   hatályos jogszabályokban meghatározott elvárásoknak. A Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. adatkezeléseivel kapcsolatos adatkezelési tájékoztató folyamatosan elérhető a
https://www.mcdonalds.com/hu/hu-hu/adatkezelesi-tajekoztato-.html
címen.
A Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. és a Progress Promotion Kft. közötti, a közös adatkezelésre vonatkozó megállapodás lényege, hogy egyes adatkezelések tekintetében a két adatkezelő közös céljaik által vezérelve, közösen végzi a személyes adatok kezelését. A megjelölt személyes adatkezeléseket illetően az adatkezelésre vonatkozó döntéseket közösen hozzák meg, azok végrehajtását illetően a feladatokat megosztják. Az érintetti jogok gyakorlásával kapcsolatos igényeket alapvetően a Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. szolgálja ki és áll kapcsolatban az érintettel, de a feladat megoldásában adatkezelő partnere is szerepet vállalhat, illetve az érintett bármelyik adatkezelőnél érvényesítheti jogait. Az adatkezelő felek a kapcsolattartásra közösen a jelen tájékoztató 4. fejezetében közzétett elérhetőségeket jelölik ki.
A jelen tájékoztatóban, ahol a Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. kerül említésre, a közös adatkezelések tekintetében a tájékoztatás megfelelően alkalmazandó a Progress Promotion Kft.-re is.
Ezúton is tájékoztatjuk az érintetteket, hogy a McDonald’s® mobilalkalmazással összefüggő adatkezelések (a jelen tájékoztató 2.5. fejezete) tekintetében a fentebb leírt közös adatkezelőkön felül az egyes McDonald’s® éttermeket üzemeltető gazdasági társaságok is további közös adatkezelők. A közös adatkezelésbe bevont adatkezelőkről és az adatkezelésekről bővebben a 2.5. fejezetben tájékoztatjuk az érintetteket.
A Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. fenntartja magának a jogot jelen tájékoztató bármikori megváltoztatására. Természetesen az esetleges változásokról kellő időben értesíti közönségét. Amennyiben kérdése lenne jelen közleményünkhöz kapcsolódóan, kérjük, írja meg nekünk, és kollégánk megválaszolja kérdését.
A Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. elkötelezett ügyfelei és partnerei személyes adatainak védelmében, kiemelten fontosnak tartja ügyfelei információs önrendelkezési jogának tiszteletben tartását. A Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. a személyes adatokat bizalmasan kezeli, és megtesz minden olyan biztonsági, technikai és szervezési intézkedést, mely az adatok biztonságát garantálja. A Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. az alábbiakban ismerteti adatkezelési gyakorlatát:
2.  A személyes adatok típusa, az adatkezelés célja, jogalapja és időtartama
A Progress Étteremhálózat Kft. adatkezelési alapelvei összhangban vannak az adatvédelemmel kapcsolatos hatályos jogszabályokkal, így különösen az alábbiakkal:
Az Európai Parlament és a Tanács (EU) 2016/679 rendelete (2016. április 27.) – a természetes személyeknek a személyes adatok kezelése tekintetében történő védelméről és az ilyen adatok szabad áramlásáról, valamint a 95/46/EK irányelv hatályon kívül helyezéséről (általános adatvédelmi rendelet, GDPR);
