Sub-policy 85
https://www.mcdonalds.com/tw/zh-tw/privacy-policy.html:
隱私權保護聲明
和德昌股份有限公司(以下稱「本公司」或「我們」)作為麥當勞之授權發展商，於經營餐飲事業及提供相關服務之過程中，將尊重每一位網路使用者的權益，包括隱私權與個人資料保護在內。為確保所有瀏覽或使用本公司營運之台灣麥當勞網站與應用程式(APP)的使用者都能夠安心地瀏覽該等網站與 APP，並使用相關服務，本公司將依下列承諾與聲明，蒐集、處理與利用網路使用者之個人資料，並妥善保護其個人資料並維護其隱私權益。
本公司所蒐集的資料及其使用方式
當網路使用者於使用本公司營運之台灣麥當勞網站或 APP 時，本公司可能基於優化使用者體驗之目的而採取 cookie 或相類似服務(例如: Google Analytics)的追蹤技術，或者為了受理網路使用者意見、調查消費者滿意度，或為提供消費者相關餐飲服務，例如：訂餐服務、外送服務、會員服務、親子活動、抱怨或申訴、抽獎活動等目的，而在各該目的之必要範圍內蒐集網路使用者的個人資料，例如：姓名、生日、地址、電話、電子郵件地址、交易資訊、網路/APP 會員資料、產品喜好、社群媒體帳號、地理位置，以及其他互動過程中使用者所提供的資料等。本公司除經由網站、APP 直接向消費者、使用者蒐集個人資料外，亦可能經由其他來源蒐集到個人資料，例如社群媒體平台，以及第三方合作夥伴取得個人資料。對於所有蒐集之資料，本公司均依相關法令及本聲明之規範，進行個人資料的處理、利用與保存。
本公司歡迎熱愛餐飲事業與麥當勞文化者，加入台灣麥當勞的營運。網路使用者將可以於本公司網站閱覽如何加入台灣麥當勞之訊息，同時，也可以了解到未來的相關發展。有興趣加入台灣麥當勞的網路使用者，將可以透過與本公司有合作關係之人力銀行進行履歷的投遞。由於該等人力資源網站所為網路使用者個人資料之蒐集、處理或利用，將受各別網站之隱私權保護政策所規範，而不在本隱私權保護聲明規範之範疇內。在此，我們呼籲網路使用者在向其他公司所營運之人力資源網站提供個人資料前，應詳細閱讀其隱私權保護政策，以保障自身相關權益。
網路使用者資料可以被分享的範圍
在遵守相同的網路使用者隱私權保護協定規範下，本公司允許麥當勞集團中的企業使用網路使用者的資料，包括麥當勞全球營運總部、關係企業或台灣麥當勞加盟店。在消費者選擇同意收到台灣麥當勞相關產品或服務訊息的情況下，本公司將會定期與不定期地發送產品或服務行銷訊息予消費者，包括如折價券或新產品介紹等等，消費者如不願意再收到訊息，仍可以取消該同意，本公司將不會再寄送相關訊息；如果消費者選擇不同意收到相關訊息，本公司將不會發送任何產品或服務行銷訊息給消費者。
部分本公司的配合廠商，在進行如完成訂購程序、協助行銷活動推廣、提供網站技術服務等等工作項目時，會接觸到本公司所蒐集的網路使用者資料，但其所使用的範圍都將只會以本公司所指定的業務範圍為準。
本公司不會出售，轉讓，或洩漏任何網路使用者相關資訊予任何麥當勞企業集團以外的其他單位。在消費者的事先同意之下，本公司會偶爾傳送由本公司商業夥伴的產品或服務訊息給消費者，本公司會在事前先徵詢消費者是否同意收到任何有關本公司商業夥伴的行銷訊息，如果消費者選擇同意，本公司會發送其商業夥伴的行銷訊息給消費者，但是不會將消費者的資料提供給其商業夥伴。
在下列情況之下，本公司保留其使用或提供網路使用者資料的權利，包括在法律的規範與要求下、在維護台灣麥當勞網站的完整與合法性的情況下、在回應網路使用者本人的要求下、在配合法律調查與公共安全的情況下等等。
關於兒童的隱私權保護
本公司對於隱私權的維護一直不遺餘力，同時引以為傲的是長期對本公司客戶所做的承諾，尤其是對與本公司最珍貴的客戶—兒童所做的溝通，我們一直特別地小心與謹慎。
除為辦理「麥麥童樂會」網站上的親子活動之外，本公司不會以其他活動名義及透過其他網站或 APP 途徑，蒐集 12 歲以下兒童的個人資料。且本公司僅接受由兒童的法定代理人(如：父母親)代理兒童報名相關親子活動，並且僅在辦理活動目的之必要範圍內，蒐集兒童的相關個人資料。但即便如此，考量到避免過度執行身分及資料驗證措施而有侵犯消費者隱私之虞，我們尚無法全面防止兒童本人自行並冒用其法定代理人的名義報名相關親子活動；或者因其於本公司所營台灣麥當勞網站或 Facebook、Instagram 等社群平台提供不實的生日資訊，致使本公司於辦理會員註冊或行銷活動時，在不知情的情況下接受 12 歲以下兒童註冊會員或報名活動之行為，並因而保有其個人資料。在此，我們呼籲家長能夠適當瞭解並管束子女的網路使用行為。同時，本公司也承諾，一旦查知兒童的上述不實行為，本公司及相關合作廠商均會立即停止使用並刪除因此所取得之兒童個人資料。
關於所蒐集來的兒童資料，將僅限於由本公司使用，或是由本公司的合作廠商，在為本公司提供技術或其他相關服務時所使用。例如，本公司的合作廠商在改進網站內容，回應顧客要求，或是主辦抽獎活動等情況。任何網路使用者資料將不會出售或轉讓予任何第三者。
連接至個人資料
本公司致力於保護每一位網路使用者所提供的個人資料，每一位使用者對於其所提供予本公司之個人資料，都有資訊自主權，得依相關個人資料保護法令之規定，向本公司查詢或複製與其有關之個人資料；於個人狀態有變動的情況下，可以要求本公司補充或更正其個人資料；於不再使用本公司所提供之服務的情況下，可以要求本公司刪除或停止處理與利用其個人資料。當消費者本人為兒童時，為保護兒童之權益，本公司僅接受與回應由兒童之法定代理人(如：父母親)所提出的要求。
本公司將在兼顧網路使用者權益保護與便利的前提下，將依經營及提供服務之內容，以電話、電子郵件、紙本、通訊軟體官方帳號、網站或 APP 等方式，受理網路使用者查詢、補充或更正、刪除其個人資料等之請求，例如：使用並註冊為本公司經營的台灣麥當勞 APP 會員者，可自行於 APP 內編輯以補充或更正其個人資料，並取消或訂閱最新優惠之郵件或簡訊，並以書面申請表之方式，請求刪除或變更帳戶等資料。同時，網路使用者可以聯絡本公司之客服部門，針對個人資料之查詢、補充或更正、刪除等提出請求，或是就相關機制提出意見或建議，本公司將適當地協助與回應使用者，並就相關意見或建議進行檢視與採取必要措施。有關客服部門之聯絡方式如下：
和德昌股份有限公司(麥當勞授權發展商) 客服部門
聯絡電話：0800-211321(手機請改撥 02-8066-1056)
電子郵件：customerservice@tw.mcd.com
Cookies 與相類似之技術的使用
"Cookies"是網站為了記錄網路使用者的活動所傳送至網路使用者設備硬碟上的一小段資料。Cookies 可以讓網站記住某些關於網路使用者的資訊，讓網路使用者在瀏覽網頁的時候更為便利。就如同現今絕大多數的網站一樣，本公司所營運之台灣麥當勞網站、APP 使用了 cookies  或相類似服務(例如: Google Analytics)以便讓使用者有一個更為愉快的網路經驗。
本公司在使用cookies或相類似服務(例如: Google Analytics)，原則僅作為客戶使用服務情形分析，所取得之資料僅為客戶群體情形，無法識別至特定個人。如分析近期網站、APP 瀏覽人次最多之頁面；或瀏覽者使用網站、APP 的時間長度等分析或利用。
我們也可能與其他合作夥伴共享cookies或相類似服務(例如: Google Analytics)資料，以分析使用者如何使用我們的網站及 APP，進而提供更符合使用者需求的廣告與網站/APP 使用體驗。
如果您不願意接受 cookies 的話，可於您所使用的網路我們或許會在台灣麥當勞網站中提供連結，以供連結至其他網站上。請參考該網站對於網路使用者隱私權保護的相關條款，本公司將不為其他網站的隱私權保護規定負責。瀏覽器設定介面中，關閉接受 cookies 的選項，或是將選項選擇為在接收到 cookies 的時候通知使用者。請點選您瀏覽器中的「說明」選項以了解關於調整接受 cookies 的方法。如果您選擇不接受 cookies，您將可能無法享受網站上所提供某些的便利功能。
連結至其他網站
我們或許會在麥當勞網站中提供連結至麥當勞以外的網站上。請參考該網站對於網路使用者隱私權保護的相關條款，麥當勞將不為其他網站的隱私權保護規定負責。
關於其他的麥當勞網站
全球所有由麥當勞企業所營運的網站，都將遵循共通的隱私權保護精神或原則性規範。但由於各個國家地區的法律規範或風土民情均有不同，具體細節的規範上亦會有所差異。但是，所有由麥當勞企業所營運的網站，在蒐集或使用網路使用者資料的同時，都將本於共通的隱私權保護規定的精神或原則，遵循我們對網路使用者一貫的承諾。
隱私權保護規定的修改
本公司將因為服務內容之調整、法令變動等必要因素修改本隱私權保護聲明之內容。若有修改，本公司將於台灣麥當勞官方網站上進行公告，建議使用者定期上網查看最新的條款內容。同時，本公司可能會以電子郵件、台灣麥當勞 APP 進行訊息推播、或以其他適當方式，主動通知網路使用者有關於本隱私權保護聲明之調整，於必要時，並將徵求使用者的同意。
與我們聯絡
如果您對本公司在保護網路使用者隱私權方面有任何問題或意見，請與我們聯絡：
和德昌股份有限公司(麥當勞授權發展商) 客服部門
聯絡電話：0800-211321(手機請改撥 02-8066-1056)
電子郵件：customerservice@tw.mcd.com
版本：2023 年 6 月 16 日
Statement about Privacy Protection
Prospect Hospitality Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as “the Company” or “we”) as the development licensee of McDonald's will respect the rights of every Internet user, including privacy and personal data protection, in the process of rendering restaurant and relevant services. To ensure that all users can browse or use the website and the app operated by McDonald's Taiwan and access relevant services with ease, we will collect, process and use the personal data of Internet users, safeguard such personal data and protect the privacy of these users according to the following commitment and declaration.
Data collected by the Company and methods of use
When Internet users access the website or app of McDonald's Taiwan operated by the Company, we may use cookies or similar tracking services (e.g., Google Analytics) to optimize the user experience, to accept the opinions of Internet users and to survey on the levels of consumers’ satisfaction, or to provide consumers with relevant food and beverage services (such as ordering, delivery, membership, parent-child bonding activities, complaints or reporting, and lucky draws). Personal data of Internet users is collected within the necessary scope for each purpose and this may include names, dates of birth, addresses, telephone numbers, emails, transaction information, website/app membership data, product preferences, social media accounts, locations and other data provided by users in the interaction process. The Company collects personal data directly from consumers and users on the website and the app, as well as from other resources such as social media and third-party partners. We process, use and retain all the collected personal data in accordance with the governance of relevant laws and this statement.
We welcome those who love the food and beverage industry and the McDonald’s culture to join McDonald's Taiwan. Internet users will be able to find out how to join McDonald's Taiwan and learn about relevant future developments from the Company website. The Internet users who are interested in joining McDonald's Taiwan will be able to submit resumes via the job sites we cooperate with. However, the collection, processing and use of Internet users’ personal data by these job sites are regulated by the privacy protection policies of the individual websites, not within the scope of privacy protection under this statement. Therefore, we urge Internet users to read in detail the privacy protection policy of the human resources site operated by other companies before providing personal data, to protect their own relevant rights.
Scope of sharable data of Internet users
Provided the adherence to the same agreement for privacy protection of Internet users, we allow the companies within the McDonald's group (including global headquarters and affiliated enterprises of McDonald's or franchised stores of McDonald's Taiwan) to use the data of Internet users. When consumers select “consent” to receive information of relevant products or services from McDonald's Taiwan, we will send consumers marketing messages about products or services (e.g., coupons and new product introduction) regularly and from time to time. If consumers are unwilling to receive such messages further, they can still cancel the consent and we will no longer send relevant messages. If consumers select “not consent” to receive relevant information, we will not send any marketing messages on any product or service to consumers.
Some of our suppliers will access the data of Internet users collected by the Company when they complete the ordering procedures, assist in marketing campaigns and provide technical services, etc. to the website. However, the scope of use shall be limited to the business specified by the Company.
We will not sell, transfer or divulge the relevant information of any Internet users to organizations outside the McDonald's group. With prior consent from consumers, we will occasionally send to consumers the product or service messages from our business partners. We will ask consumers in advance whether they consent to the receipt of any marketing information about our business partners. If they select “consent”, we will send the marketing information from our business partners to consumers, without providing consumers’ data to these businesses partners.
Under the following circumstances, we reserve the right to use or provide the data of Internet users. This includes legal regulations and requirements; maintenance of the integrity and lawfulness of the McDonald's Taiwan website, responding to the request from an Internet user; and cooperating with legal investigations and for public safety, etc.
About privacy protection of children
We spare no efforts in privacy protection. We are proud of our long-standing commitment to our customers. We have always been extra cautious and careful in communication with our most cherished customers – children.
Except for the parent-child bonding activity “Fun for McDonalds’ Children” shown on the website, we will not collect the personal data of children under 12 years old in the name of other campaigns or via other website/app. Meanwhile, we only accept the registration by children’s legal representatives (e.g., parents) for relevant parent-child bonding activities and only collect the personal data of children within the scope necessary for the organization of events. Despite these measures in place and considering the possibility of infringement of consumers’ privacy as a result of over-execution of identity and data verification, we are not able to fully prevent children from registering for relevant parent-child bonding activities themselves or by using the names of their legal representatives. When handling membership registrations or marketing activities, we may unknowingly accept the membership registration or event sign-up by children under 12 years old and end up retaining their personal data as a result of false dates of birth information provided to the McDonalds’ website or by social media such as Facebook and Instagram. We hence urge parents to gain an appropriate understanding and manage the Internet activities of children. Meanwhile, we promise that the Company and relevant cooperating companies shall stop the use of acquired personal data of children and delete such data immediately once we have identified the abovementioned dishonest behavior of children.
The children’s data collected shall be limited to use by the Company or by the Company’s cooperating partners when rendering technical or other relevant services to the Company (such as improvement of website contents, responding to customers’ requests or organizing lucky draws for the Company). No data of Internet users will be sold or transferred to any third party.
Regarding personal data
We strive to protect the personal data provided by each Internet user. Each user has the right to informational self-determination on the personal data they provide to the Company. They may inquire with the Company about their personal data or request duplication of such data about them according to the relevant rules prescribed by the Personal Data Protection Act. They may ask the Company to supplement or rectify their personal data in case of change in personal circumstances. They may ask the Company to delete or stop the processing and the use of their personal data when they no longer use the services provided by the Company. If consumers are children, we only accept and respond to the request from their legal representative (e.g., parents) in order to protect the rights of children.
We will balance between the protection of Internet users’ rights and the provision of convenient services, based on the business nature and the service menu, when we handle inquiries from Internet users and requests for supplementing, rectification or deletion of their personal data via telephone, over emails, with paper-based correspondence or through our official account on messaging apps, website or app. For example, the registered members may use the McDonald's Taiwan app operated by the Company to supplement or rectify their personal data on the app; cancel or subscribe to the newsletters or text messages about the updates on promotional offers; and request for deletion or modification of account data via written application forms. Moreover, Internet users may contact our Customer Care Department to inquire about personal data, request for supplementing, rectification or deletion of personal data or provide opinions or suggestions about relevant mechanisms. We will assist and respond to users appropriately, review the opinions or suggestions and adopt necessary measures.
The contact details of Customer Care Department are as follows:
Customer Care Department of Prospect Hospitality Co., Ltd. (development licensee of McDonald's)
Telephone: 0800-211321 (02-8066-1056 if dialed from a mobile phone)
Email: customerservice@tw.mcd.com
Use of cookies and similar technologies
Cookies are small pieces of data sent by websites to the hard-disks of Internet users in order to record the activities of these Internet users. Cookies allow websites to remember certain information about Internet users, so that webpage browsing becomes more convenient for Internet users. Same as most of the websites today, the McDonald's Taiwan website and app operated by the Company use cookies or similar services (e.g., Google Analytics) to create a more pleasant online experience for users.
In principle, we only use cookies or similar services (e.g., Google Analytics) to analyze how services are used by customers. The data obtained is about customer groups, without identification of specific individuals. Examples are the analytics of webpages and app pages browsed by most people recently, analysis and use of browsing lengths by website/app users.
We may also share cookies or similar services (e.g., Google Analytics) data with cooperating partners for analysis of how users utilize our website and app, in order to provide advertisements and website/app user experience specific to users’ needs.
If you are unwilling to accept cookies, you may disable cookies via the setup of your browser or select for cookie notices, to be informed when cookies arrive. Please select “Instructions” on your browser in order to understand the methods to adjust and accept cookies. If you opt not to accept cookies, you may not be able to enjoy some easy-to-use functions on the website.
Links to other websites
We may provide links on the McDonald’s Taiwan website to other websites. Please refer to the relevant clauses on these websites regarding the protection of Internet users’ privacy. We will not be responsible for the privacy protection rules of other websites.
About other McDonald’s websites
All the websites operated by McDonald’s around the world comply with shared spirit of privacy protection or regulations in principle. However, legal requirements or local conventions vary across countries and regions. There are also differences in detailed rules. That said, all the websites operated by McDonald’s companies adhere to our shared spirit or principle in privacy protection and consistent commitment to Internet users when collecting or using data of Internet users.
Amendment to privacy protection rules
We will need to amend the contents of this privacy protection statement due to adjustment of services and changes in laws. We will announce any amendments via the official website of McDonald’s Taiwan. Users are advised to regularly check out the newest clauses. Meanwhile, we may broadcast information via emails, on the McDonald’s Taiwan app or via other appropriate means to notify Internet users of the adjustment to this privacy protection statement and when necessary, obtain the consent of users.
Contact details
Please contact us if you have any questions or opinions about the Company’s protection of Internet users’ privacy.
Customer Care Department of Prospect Hospitality Co., Ltd. (development licensee of McDonald's)
Telephone: 0800-211321(02-8066-1056 if dialed from a mobile phone)
Email: customerservice@tw.mcd.com
